        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @Messidinho- I think it's more to do with WhoScored estimating when Stones will be rested than having a blinding bias. He has played many games in succession including (surprisingly) the recent league cup tie and I'm guessing that they consider Kompany to be a better one-off option than Otamendi. Stones has been excellent for about a full year now, something which had an air of inevitability about it given his talent and the typical trajectory of young CBs. Laporte was fantastic in La Liga, in declining team, and has carried that on through his City career to date. Fans are opinionated and mine is that City's CB pairing have been superb, especially given the defensive detritus at FB. Pep's style is the most difficult in some ways but the most forgiving in others. For quick CBs who are good on the ball, Pep's system is ideal plus the general dominance offers a protection and the CBs aren't criticised by him for making a high risk mistake which could have produced high reward.
